Team Members

Project Manager: C. Sai Pavan

Documentation Lead: G. Harika

Lead Developer: K. Wayiz

QA Lead: B. Akash

1. Team Purpose

The purpose of this team is to collaboratively design and develop the Blood Bank Management System by following software engineering and agile development principles. The team aims to deliver a high-quality, reliable, and well-documented software product within the given timeline.

2. Roles & Responsibilities

Project Manager:
Plans project activities, assigns tasks, tracks progress, and coordinates between team members and faculty.

Documentation Lead:
Prepares and maintains project documents such as SRS, design documents, reports, and ensures proper formatting and submission.

Lead Developer:
Designs system architecture, implements core functionalities, integrates modules, and supports team members in development.

QA Lead:
Tests the application, identifies bugs, validates requirements, and ensures the final product meets quality standards.

3. Working Norms

All team members must attend meetings regularly and participate actively.

Tasks must be completed within the agreed deadlines.

Any delay or issue should be communicated immediately to the Project Manager.

Team members should respect each otherâ€™s ideas and maintain a professional attitude.

Decisions will be made collectively after discussion.

4. Communication Plan

Primary communication will be through WhatsApp / Google Meet.

Weekly progress meetings will be conducted.

Important updates will be shared with all team members without delay.

5. Conflict Resolution

Conflicts will be discussed openly within the team.

If unresolved, the issue will be escalated to the faculty/project guide.

Mutual respect and understanding will be maintained at all times.

6. Commitment

All team members agree to:

Contribute equally to the project

Follow the defined working norms

Maintain honesty, responsibility, and teamwork

This agreement is accepted by all team members to ensure smooth execution of the project.
